28/06/2006
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Police announced on Tuesday (27 June) the arrest of a local man suspected of plotting a terrorist act. 
Florin Lesch, a Muslim convert, was stopped on Monday as he drove a car bomb toward the city of Timisoara. 
According to police, the explosive device was made of gas canisters. 
Lesch had been under surveillance since he travelled to Bosnia and Herzegovina last year to convert to Islam. 
(Romania Libera, Azi, Nine o'clock - 28/06/06; AP, BBC, Rompres - 27/06/06)
